Definition: dignified and somber in manner or character and committed to keeping promises
Example: a grave God-fearing man; a quiet sedate nature; as sober as a judge; a solemn promise; the judge was solemn as he pronounced sentence
Synonyms: noun, attribute, graveness, gravity, sedate, sedateness, sober, soberness, solemn, solemness, feeling, solemnity, dignified, and, somber, in, manner, or, character, committed, to, keeping, promises, a, God-fearing, man, quiet, nature, as, judge, promise, the, was, he, pronounced, sentence
Category: adj.all
